  "target_response": {
    "text": "Your own numbers say you're running a real gap even if you feel okay: your 7-day average is 6 h of sleep, about 1.5 h short of your estimated 7.5 h need, and your tracker has you carrying 176 min of accumulated debt. Feeling fine counts for something, but adaptation to short sleep famously hides its costs — subjective alertness often stops tracking the underlying deficit. Rather than take the need estimate on faith, run the experiment: for two weeks, shift bedtime earlier by half an hour with your wake time fixed, then compare morning HRV and daytime energy against this period. If nothing improves, your personal need may genuinely sit lower than the estimate — it is an estimate, not a prescription. If mornings get noticeably easier, the six-hour habit was quietly charging you.",
